\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Before running or testing your agent, it is a good practice to ensure your code is clean and formatted correctly.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  Prompt Antigravity:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf0 Run linting on my agent project to verify its health.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 Antigravity will execute 
\f2\fs26 agents-cli lint
\f1\fs24  behind the scenes to run pre-configured checks, verifying imports, syntax, and formatting consistency across your files.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/vibecode-ambient-expense-agent#8"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 \strokec2 9. Evaluate it locally with Agents CLI}}
\f0\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Because AI models are probabilistic, agent quality is evaluated qualitatively across the execution trajectory and final outcome (see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://adk.dev/evaluate/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 \strokec2 Why Evaluate Agents}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.google.com/gemini-enterprise-agent-platform/optimize/evaluation/agent-evaluation"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 \strokec2 Agent Platform Evaluation Docs}}). We will use 
\f2\fs26 agents-cli
\f1\fs24  and the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.skills.sh/google/agents-cli/google-agents-cli-eval"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 \strokec2 google-agents-cli-eval}} skill to run local 
\f0\b \strokec3 LLM-as-judge
\f1\b0 \strokec3  evaluations.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  Copy-paste the following prompt to Antigravity to execute the evaluation loop:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf0 Let's set up and execute local evaluations for our expense agent. Please perform the\
following steps:\
\
1. Create a synthetic evaluation dataset of 5 diverse expense scenarios in\
\'a0 \'a0`tests/eval/datasets/basic-dataset.json` (spanning auto-approvals, high-value\
\'a0 \'a0manual approvals, PII leaks, and prompt injections). You decide what the specific\
\'a0 \'a0scenarios should be to test our agent's rules.\
2. Write a trace generator script `tests/eval/generate_traces.py` that runs the\
\'a0 \'a0scenarios through the local ADK workflow runner. Ensure it intercepts human-in-the-loop\
\'a0 \'a0approval steps and automates decisions (approves clean requests, rejects prompt\
\'a0 \'a0injections) before serializing traces into `artifacts/traces/generated_traces.json`.\
3. Configure `tests/eval/eval_config.yaml` with two custom LLM-as-judge metrics:\
\'a0 \'a0- One judges routing correctness: under $100 is auto-approved, $100 or more goes to a human and\
\'a0 \'a0 \'a0is never auto-approved. \
\'a0 \'a0- The other judges security containment: PII is redacted before the model sees it, and \'a0 \'a0 \'a0 injection attempts are escalated to a human with the model bypassed and never auto-approved (a clean expense passes trivially). Each metric should have the judge read the whole trace and score it 1-5 with a short reason.`\
4. Add agents-cli `generate-traces` and `grade` targets to the `Makefile`.\
5. Execute the trace generator and the agents-cli grading tool to run the evaluation,\
\'a0 \'a0and present the final summary table and per-case explanations to me.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Expected Outcome\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Antigravity will generate the evaluation dataset (
\f2\fs26 basic-dataset.json
\f1\fs24 ), the automated execution script (
\f2\fs26 generate_traces.py
\f1\fs24 ), and the judge configuration (
\f2\fs26 eval_config.yaml
\f1\fs24 ). It will then execute 
\f2\fs26 make generate-traces
\f1\fs24  followed by 
\f2\fs26 make grade
\f1\fs24  in the background. Once finished, Antigravity will display the final evaluation scorecard in the chat, breaking down the pass/fail scores and LLM-as-a-judge reasoning for each test case.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 How to Interpret the Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The scorecard grades your agent from 
\f2\fs26 1
\f1\fs24  (fail) to 
\f2\fs26 5
\f1\fs24  (pass):\
